cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the problem of semantic segmentation of 3D point clouds using neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also introduces a novel local feature aggregation module, which involves processing and analyzing geometric details, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Additionally, the paper deals with large-scale point clouds, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) in the context of semantic segmentation, which could fall under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) category.
